flowRoot.flowPara: "Auto" is a toggle button - pressing it moves the sliders to an automatically determined position. The sliders can still be moved independently - manually changing them pushes the auto button back out (but does not reset).

text.tspan: - "magic" mode by default, detailed controls secondary

flowRoot.flowPara: Cropping is specific in that it needs to be applied and yet allow re-editing. I suggest to expand and collapse every tool by clicking its header. All other tools expose editing with sliders on the side, but perhaps we'll allow onscreen position for some filters (spot removal).
Crop and rotate - while mode is active, the image is reduced in size, in order to leave room for dragging the crop controls and for the fine-rotation control.
When crop is opened for the first time, the whole image is included inside the crop area and "free" is selected for the aspect ratio.
When the image has been cropped or fine-rotated, excluded areas are semi-opaque. The excluded area is only shown while crop and rotate is active, and is hidden in other edit modes.
When an image has been fine-rotated, it should be automatically cropped so that the image always fills the frame. It should not be possible to crop outside of the visible image.
